    ## Creating an Abstract Data Type to Organize Musical Data        
    &lt;div class="forYouToDo"&gt;
        &lt;ol start="4"&gt;
            &lt;li&gt;
                &lt;div class="sidenoteBig"&gt;
                    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Pitch&lt;/em&gt; is the amount of highness or lowness of a musical note; the pitch value goes in the first input slot of the &lt;code&gt;play note&lt;/code&gt; block.&lt;/p&gt;
                    &lt;p&gt;The &lt;em&gt;length&lt;/em&gt; of a note is the amount of time that the note plays (the number of beats); the length value goes in the second slot of &lt;code&gt;play note&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;  
                &lt;/div&gt;
                Create a &lt;code&gt;note&lt;/code&gt; ADT to manage the pitch and length of each note in a song.
                &lt;ol&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        Create the constructor:&lt;br /&gt;
