                        Find the &lt;code&gt;set (&lt;/code&gt;&lt;var&gt;output&lt;/var&gt;&lt;code&gt;) to...&lt;/code&gt; instruction and &lt;strong&gt;change the input text&lt;/strong&gt; to a short text string of your choosing. The reported binary sequence will be stored in the &lt;var&gt;output&lt;/var&gt; variable with quotes around it.&lt;br /&gt;
                        &lt;img class="indent" src="/img/6-computers/set-output-to-translate-text.png" alt="set (output) to (translate text (Beauty and Joy of Computing) to binary sequence)" title="set (output) to (translate text (Beauty and Joy of Computing) to binary sequence)" /&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
                    &lt;li&gt;
                        Access the output by right-clicking (or control-clicking) on the OUTPUT watcher on the stage and choosing "export..." The binary sequence will download as a text file. Copy the binary sequence out of the file, but not the quotes.&lt;br /&gt;
                        &lt;img class="indent" src="/img/6-computers/exporting-output-watcher.png" alt="image of output watcher on stage storing a binary sequence with the drop-down menu open and  'export...' option selected" title="image of output watcher on stage storing a binary sequence with the drop-down menu open and  'export...' option selected" /&gt;
                    &lt;/li&gt;
